      "writtenOn": "2016-05-06T17:43:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the tip :)\n\nThe particular reason for the lock:\n\nWhen using GL fence sync (to improve buffer flipping/app transitions), there can be multiple threads that could wait on a single fence command\u0027s completion. We might get better performance using this lock when multiple threads initiate waits on a single OpenGL fence sync object in a short time; rather than allowing just one thread to read from a map at a time, allow several.\n\nJust using a regular lock seems fine for the moment in that application, though. Overall, I mostly thought this would be nice to have in general.",
